# 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

> [!WARNING]
> **KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Common Pitfalls**
> 1. **Confusing Overloading vs Overriding** — Overloading is *compile-time polymorphism* (different parameter lists, same class). Overriding is *runtime polymorphism* (same signature, parent-child). Students often write "same method name with different parameters" for overriding — this loses **2 marks** instantly.
> 2. **Forgetting that static methods are HIDDEN, not overridden** — A common error is saying "static methods are overridden at runtime." Wrong. They are resolved at compile time.
> 3. **Writing `super()` after other statements in a constructor** — The compiler demands `super()` or `this()` to be the **very first line**. Placing it second causes a compile error.
> 4. **Confusing `System.in` (InputStream) with `System.in.readLine()`** — `System.in` is a byte stream and does NOT have `readLine()`. You must wrap it with `BufferedReader` and `InputStreamReader`.
> 5. **Not closing I/O streams** — In a 14-mark program question, forgetting to close the stream in `finally` block or using try-with-resources costs **1–2 marks**.
> 6. **Using `FileWriter` without second argument for append mode** — Students often say "append mode" but write `new FileWriter("file.txt")` (which overwrites).

