## Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Question 1 [KTU University Exam — May 2023 Model]
**What is method overriding in Java? State any four rules that must be followed while overriding a method.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

Method overriding is a feature of Java in which a subclass provides a specific implementation of a method that is already defined in its superclass. It is used to achieve runtime polymorphism.

Four rules for method overriding:
1. The method in the subclass must have the **same name** and **parameter list** as in the parent class.
2. The **return type** must be the same or a **covariant subtype** of the parent's return type.
3. The **access modifier** of the overriding method cannot be more restrictive than that of the overridden method.
4. The overriding method can throw **fewer or narrower checked exceptions**, but cannot throw new or broader checked exceptions.

*(+1 mark for definition, +2 marks for any four rules)*

