## Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid Revision Checklist)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Final Revision Checklist — Method Overriding, super, and I/O Basics**

### Method Overriding
- ✓ Requires an **IS-A relationship** (inheritance).
- ✓ Method name + parameter list must be **identical** to the parent.
- ✓ Return type must be the **same or covariant**.
- ✓ Access modifier **cannot be more restrictive** (e.g., cannot reduce `public` to `private`).
- ✓ **Static, final, and private methods cannot be overridden**.
- ✓ Constructors are **never inherited**, so they cannot be overridden.
- ✓ Overriding enables **runtime polymorphism via Dynamic Method Dispatch** (vtable lookup).
- ✓ Always use the `@Override` annotation — it lets the compiler verify the override.

### The `super` Keyword
- ✓ Refers to the **immediate parent class object**, not the parent class itself.
- ✓ Three uses: `super.field`, `super.method()`, `super()`/`super(args)`.
- ✓ `super()` or `this()` **must be the first line** of a constructor — they cannot coexist.
- ✓ If neither is written explicitly, the compiler **auto-inserts `super()`**.
- ✓ If the parent has no no-arg constructor and the child does not explicitly chain, **compile error** occurs.
- ✓ Use `super.method()` to **extend** parent behavior rather than fully replace it.

### Java I/O Basics
- ✓ The `java.io` package is organized into **byte streams** and **character streams**.
- ✓ **Byte streams** (`InputStream` / `OutputStream`): for binary data.
- ✓ **Character streams** (`Reader` / `Writer`): for text data with Unicode support.
- ✓ **Standard streams**: `System.in` (InputStream), `System.out` (PrintStream), `System.err` (PrintStream).
- ✓ **Buffering** (`BufferedReader`, `BufferedWriter`, `BufferedInputStream`, `BufferedOutputStream`) significantly improves I/O performance.
- ✓ `BufferedReader.readLine()` is the most common way to read text line-by-line.
- ✓ `Scanner` is convenient for **keyboard input** with parsing methods like `nextInt()` and `nextLine()`.
- ✓ **Always close I/O streams** — preferably with **try-with-resources** (Java 7+).
- ✓ `FileWriter(path, true)` enables **append mode**; default is overwrite.
- ✓ **Decorator Pattern** is used heavily: wrapper classes add features (buffering, primitive reading) on top of basic streams.

### Common Exam Traps to Avoid
- ❌ Don't say "static methods are overridden" — they are **hidden**.
- ❌ Don't place `super()` after other statements in a constructor.
- ❌ Don't try to call `System.in.readLine()` — `System.in` is a byte stream, wrap it first.
- ❌ Don't forget to close streams — use try-with-resources.
- ❌ Don't confuse **overloading** (compile-time, same class, different params) with **overriding** (runtime, parent-child, same params).
