### **Question B (14 Marks) — Alternative Choice: [KTU University Exam — May 2023]**

**(a) [7 Marks]** With a suitable Java program, demonstrate how the order of catch blocks matters when handling multiple exceptions. What is the "unreachable catch block" compile-time error? Illustrate with an example showing both incorrect and correct orderings.

**(b) [7 Marks]** Differentiate between the traditional multiple catch blocks and the Java 7 multi-catch syntax. Provide a comparative example and explain the `final` variable constraint in multi-catch.

