> [!WARNING]
> **⚠️ KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning — Common Pitfalls:**
> 
> 1. **Reversing Catch Order (Deducts 2-3 marks):** Students frequently place `catch(Exception e)` before specific catches. This is a **compile-time error**, and the program will not run.
> 
> 2. **Confusing Checked vs Unchecked Exceptions (Deducts 1-2 marks):** `ArithmeticException`, `ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException`, and `NullPointerException` are **unchecked** (RuntimeException subclasses) and do not require `throws` declaration. Students often incorrectly add `throws` clauses.
> 
> 3. **Multi-Catch with Inheritance (Deducts 2 marks):** Writing `catch(IOException | FileNotFoundException e)` is a compile error. Students must remember that the alternatives must be **disjoint** (no inheritance relationship).
> 
> 4. **Forgetting that Only ONE Catch Executes (Deducts 1 mark):** Students sometimes write code assuming all matching catch blocks will execute sequentially. Only the **first match** runs.
> 
> 5. **Using `printStackTrace()` Without Explanation (Deducts 0.5 mark):** While acceptable, KTU examiners prefer explanations of `getMessage()` and `toString()` for proper exception handling demonstrations.

