## 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember ✍

- **MVC = Model + View + Controller**, a **compound design pattern**.
- **Model** = data + business rules; **no UI imports allowed**.
- **View** = passive UI; **no business logic**; reads from Model.
- **Controller** = mediator; **only component that knows both M and V**.
- **Coupling rule:** Model ↔ View coupling is **zero**; View → Controller is **1-way** (event delegation).
- **Patterns inside MVC:** Observer (Model→View), Strategy (View→Controller), Composite (UI tree).
- **MVC variants:** MVP (Presenter replaces Controller, View is fully passive), MVVM (ViewModel + data binding).
- **Java implementation:** Model = POJO, View = `JFrame` subclass, Controller = class with `ActionListener` wiring.
- **Real-world use:** Spring MVC, Django, Ruby on Rails, ASP.NET, JavaFX, Swing.
- **Equation to remember:** $\text{Display}_{t+1} = \rho(V,\, M(\mu(C, U_t)))$ — the formal request cycle.
- **Golden exam line:** *"The Controller is the brain, the Model is the heart, the View is the face."*
- **Keyword in KTU answer scripts:** always write "*separation of concerns*" and "*decoupling*" at least once — they are scoring buzzwords.

