## 4.3 JDBC Connectivity — Sequence Diagram

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Java Application
    participant DM as DriverManager
    participant Drv as JDBC Driver
    participant Conn as Connection
    participant Stmt as PreparedStatement
    participant DB as Database Server

    App->>DM: getConnection(url, user, pwd)
    DM->>Drv: Find driver matching URL
    Drv-->>DM: Driver accepts URL
    DM->>Conn: Open TCP socket and authenticate
    Conn-->>App: Connection object returned

    App->>Conn: prepareStatement(SQL with ?)
    Conn-->>App: PreparedStatement object

    App->>Stmt: setInt(1, 101)
    App->>Stmt: setString(2, "Ananya")
    App->>Stmt: executeUpdate()
    Stmt->>DB: Send SQL over TCP
    DB-->>Stmt: rowsAffected = 1
    Stmt-->>App: Returns 1

    App->>Conn: close()
    Conn->>DB: Close socket and release resources
```

### Diagram Reading Guide

- **Solid arrows** = method calls.
- **Dashed arrows** = return values.
- This sequence represents the **lifecycle of a JDBC interaction**, from connection open to connection close.
