### Question B (14 Marks) — Choice Option 2

> **[KTU University Exam - Sample Model Paper 2024]**
> *Explain the JTextField class in Java Swing with its constructors and important methods. Write a Java program to create a login form with two JTextFields (username and password with masking) and a JButton that displays a welcome message with the entered username.*

#### (a) JTextField Theory — 7 Marks

**Definition (2 marks):**
`JTextField` is a Swing component (`javax.swing.JTextField`) that allows the user to **edit a single line of unformatted text**. It is a subclass of `JTextComponent` and is the Swing-recommended replacement for AWT's `TextField`.

**Constructors (2.5 marks):**

| Constructor | Use |
|---|---|
| `JTextField()` | Empty field, default width. |
| `JTextField(String text)` | Pre-filled text. |
| `JTextField(int columns)` | Empty field with N character columns. |
| `JTextField(String text, int columns)` | Both pre-filled text and column count. |

**Important Methods (2.5 marks):**

- `String getText()` — Retrieves the current text.
- `void setText(String t)` — Sets/replaces the text.
- `void setEditable(boolean b)` — Enables or disables editing.
- `void setEchoChar(char c)` — Masks input (for passwords).
- `void setColumns(int n)` — Sets preferred width in columns.
- `void addActionListener(ActionListener l)` — Listens for Enter key.
- `void setHorizontalAlignment(int align)` — Aligns text LEFT/CENTER/RIGHT.

#### (b) Login Form Program — 7 Marks

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;
import java.awt.event.*;

public class LoginForm extends JFrame implements ActionListener {

    JTextField userField, passField;
    JLabel messageLabel;

    public LoginForm() {
        setTitle("Login Form - KTU 2024");
        setSize(350, 180);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE);
        setLayout(new GridLayout(3, 2, 10, 10));

        add(new JLabel("Username:"));
        userField = new JTextField(15);
        add(userField);

        add(new JLabel("Password:"));
        passField = new JTextField(15);
        passField.setEchoChar('*');              // Mask password input.
        add(passField);

        JButton loginBtn = new JButton("Login");
        loginBtn.addActionListener(this);
        add(loginBtn);

        messageLabel = new JLabel("");
        add(messageLabel);

        setVisible(true);
    }

    @Override
    public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
        String username = userField.getText();
        String password = new String(passField.getText());

        if (username.isEmpty() || password.isEmpty()) {
            messageLabel.setText("Please fill all fields.");
        } else {
            messageLabel.setText("Welcome, " + username + "!");
            userField.setText("");
            passField.setText("");
            userField.requestFocus();
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        new LoginForm();
    }
}
```

